  "prompt": "Is the test taker report for GMAT accessible immediately after the test ? It\u2019s not the official score report that GMAC sends after 15-20 days.",
  "response": "After completing the GMAT exam, you will receive an unofficial score report immediately upon finishing the test. This report includes your scores for the Quantitative, Verbal, Integrated Reasoning, and Total sections. However, it does not include the Analytical Writing Assessment (AWA) score, as that requires human evaluation and takes longer to process.\n\nThis unofficial score report is available before you leave the testing center, and you have the option to cancel your scores if you are not satisfied with your performance. If you choose to accept your scores, GMAC will send you an official score report within 15-20 days, which will include all sections, including the AWA score.\n\nSo, to answer your question, yes, you will have access to a test taker report (unofficial score report) immediately after the test, but it will not include the AWA score.",
